cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.FL, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with linear orders and their automatic presentations. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic arguments. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses limitations on the class of automatic structures. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with automata reading words with arbitrary linear orders. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves some game-theoretic concepts such as well-founded order trees.
